      "q": "How much does Department of Commerce spend on contracts?",
      "a": "Department of Commerce has spent $3.2B on contracts in FY2026 to date. The agency obligated those funds across 5,967 awards with an average award size of $530K, and obligations fell 23.9% year over year. All figures are contract obligations and current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date)."
    },
    {
      "q": "What does Commerce buy?",
      "a": "Commerce primarily buys information technology and professional services, led by Other Computer Related Services $568M, Computer Systems Design Services $480M, and Custom Computer Programming Services $331M in FY2026 to date. Additional notable categories are All Other Publishers $215M, Ship Building and Repairing $144M, and Administrative Management and General Management Consulting Services $134M."
